The term "operational statistics" includes total generation, total maintenance hours, and average downtime hours for each plant per year; 
"plant information" encompasses nameplate capacity, plant type, location, status, commission date, and decommission date if applicable; 
"utility company details" refers to the name of the utility company, contact email, address, phone number, and website; 
"latest document information" includes the type of document, file path, version, and description, assuming the latest document is the one with the most recent upload date.

sql:
SELECT plant_id, SUM(maintenance_hours) AS total_maintenance_hours
FROM operating_years
GROUP BY plant_id;

SELECT COUNT(*) as document_count
FROM plant_documents
WHERE plant_id = 1;

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_operating_years
FROM operating_years
WHERE plant_id = 1;

SELECT plant_id, COUNT(DISTINCT document_type) AS document_type_count
FROM plant_documents
GROUP BY plant_id;

