- In this context, 'High Downtime' refers to a situation where a power plant experiences more than 100 hours of downtime per year on average, indicating potential issues with reliability or maintenance; 
- 'Low Downtime' is the opposite, indicating fewer than 100 hours of downtime per year on average, suggesting better reliability or maintenance; 
- The calculation of average annual generation and downtime hours per year helps in evaluating the efficiency and reliability of different power plant types.
